  "prompt": "I am having problems with my friend. She is awesome, but she recently got a boyfriend. I just miss the way we once were. She's all over him and her other best friend. What should I do?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear that you're feeling this way. It can be really challenging when friendships change, especially when someone gets into a new relationship. Here are some steps you might consider taking:\n\n1. **Communicate Your Feelings**: Talk to your friend about how you're feeling. Be honest but also considerate. Use \"I\" statements to express your emotions, such as \"I miss spending time with you\" or \"I feel left out when you're with your boyfriend.\" This can help avoid sounding accusatory.\n\n2. **Set Up Time Together**: Try to plan activities that you can do together, just the two of you. This can help maintain your connection and give you both a chance to catch up.\n\n3. **Join Group Activities**: If she\u2019s spending time with her boyfriend and other friends, try to join in on some of these activities. This way, you can still be part of her life and potentially even bond with new people.\n\n4. **Pursue Your Own Interests**: Focus on your own hobbies or interests, and even consider spending time with other friends. This can help fill the gap you\u2019re feeling and provide you with other sources of support and fun.\n\n5. **Respect Her Relationship**: Try to understand that her relationship is important to her. Even if you\u2019re feeling left out, it\u2019s healthy for her to spend time with her boyfriend.\n\nFriendships can evolve over time, and it\u2019s important to navigate these changes with open communication and understanding. It might feel challenging now, but addressing your feelings and finding ways to adjust can help maintain your friendship in the long run.",
